  "texts": [
    "This procedure is crucial for time series forecasting because it helps the models more precisely identify patterns and trends in the data and produce forecasts for future values.",
    "If the data was found to be non-stationary, it is made stationary by first-order differencing.",
    "The data is then used to get ACF and PACF plots to determine the order of the AR and MA parts in different time series models.",
    "The second dataset is collected from the company chargeMOD and contained charging sessions of different users.",
    "Since the charging activity dataset is further grouped for AC and DC stations and two, three, and four-wheeler charging session data."
  ]
}